Great Food and Customer Service which is actually ‚ÄúCustomer First‚Äù.

This is a frequent place to have good Coffee, Teas, Breakfast and Lunch with terrific sandwiches that include my favorite the Grilled Lobster Sandwich and the Breakfast Sandwiches theses are made fresh and taste just right.

The Owner is a Genuine Businessman and certainly treats everyone with class and respect there‚Äôs a good vibe when you come in and make your order to go or eat in.

Even though Starbucks is next door it‚Äôs not the same, the menu here is worth the stop and walk-in you can actually have a good meal with Clam Chowder and a Grilled Sandwich that is made to order with a fabulous Iced Hibiscus Green Tea with a touch of Ginger-mint you can‚Äôt compare.

Cupcake Espresso Bar has it down right and no one will be disappointed.<//text>

< text>
We frequent La Jolla and were recommended to check out ASAP IVs during our trip for some much needed rehydration. Sign up was super easy and we were able to schedule same day appointments. They are located within Livkraft, which is a wellness spa, with infrared saunas and float pods among other services. The facility was very COVID conscious and our temperatures were taken after arriving. Within a few minutes the nurse took us to the room for our treatment. Chairs were very comfortable and the room was calming. The nurse was very personable and easily placed the IVs with minimal discomfort. Before I knew it my IV was flowing! Took about 30 minutes or so, the nurse came out and checked on us a few times to make sure we were okay. After another patron left, their seat was immediately sanitized and cleaned, so they are taking the necessary precautions which is reassuring. Next thing I knew my IV was done, I felt great and we were on our way! They have multiple options for IVs depending on what you want, which is really convenient. This is their only current in-person location, but the nurse told me they will travel to wherever you are and can do this in the comfort of your own home, a huge plus! Overall it was a great experience, the nurse was awesome, and we felt better afterwards. Highly recommend ASAP IVs!!< /text>

<name>Kris Schultz<//name><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNqRxpDAUQufOG1thYnAOv3p5PgJuwzR0EfrJAW=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOBts5HWCEHNrUbxAS5g22Cap4EeCQ3zSMWIA4X=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><Rate>5</Rate><date>1619713849580<//date>< review>
Top to bottom extremely happy with this company and would recommend them to anyone in the greater Sacramento area.

After seeing some of the work they did for a family member we had 2 sliding doors installed both in our living room and bedroom. From the minute when Taylor, the design consultant, came over we knew we were in good hands. The install was all done in 1 day for both doors very professionally by Serge. Everyone we interacted with at Reliable was on time and extremely responsive.

Some things people don't often think about- Reliable carries adequate liability insurance, products were backed by warranty, all employees are W2. All this were very important to us beyond just the work they did.

Great product, great price, excellent install. Not much more you can ask for, Reliable will be our first call going forward with all home improvement projects.

Here are some after and before pics of the work they did.</review>

< Text>
This is our third project with Reliable Home improvement.  That is probably the best review right there.  The current project was a granite look, colored, concrete walkway and patio in our backyard. <user>102255332302897890660<//user>< name>
Lia Tucker<//name>
<Date>1626271906039< /Date><Rating>5</Rating>< review>
We chose Reliable Home Improvement to remodel the wet area of our guest bathroom. I had found them using a Google search and saw that they had rather good reviews. We met with Cliff to get our estimate and he was very professional and friendly. He was very upfront with us about cost and what was involved with the remodel. We were worried about water damage behind the shower wall. All three companies we got estimates from said they couldn't give us an idea of cost of repair for the water damage since they couldn't see behind the wall. Anyway, in the end we went with Reliable. Cliff did warn us about the start time for the project. They were scheduling out six months. We were expecting this because COVID has slowed manufacturing way way down so getting the fixtures we wanted could take a long time. We met with Cliff in March and all of our bathroom fixtures came in the beginning of June. Reliable started our project towards the end of June. Laura was our project contact. She came out and met with us and gave us all the info we needed to pick out fixtures. She was also very friendly and very professional. Both she and Cliff were very knowledgeable. This is our first home so obviously we know nothing about remodeling ANYTHING. We had A LOT of questions. Jason was our installer. He was great to work with. He was very professional and really friendly. My husband and I work from home and we were worried about noise and such while the bathroom was getting redone. Jason did his best to keep the noise to a minimum. As much as you can when you‚Äôre demolishing a bathroom. Jason made sure to get our input on placement and installation of things before putting them in. Our bathtub we had ordered had somehow got broken during shipment. Jason and Reliable made every effort to get a replacement tub right away. The project was only setback a day. The project took about two weeks to complete. The end result was absolutely amazing! Our new bathtub, water fixtures, and tile are gorgeous! Everything came out looking so good. Jason did an incredible job. There were a couple issues that needed to be taken care of post installation. Jason came out the same day and fixed them. With no issues and no hidden costs at the end. Working with Reliable was a wonderful experience. They may not the cheapest contractors in town, but they are also not the most expensive. Trust me, you get what you pay for. I would highly highly recommend!<//review>

< pics>
None< /pics>
< text>
We used Reliable Home Improvement to remove our old driveway and pour a new driveway, as well as widen our cement path on the side of our garage. We were approached due to them doing work in the area and was given a 10% coupon if we hired them. The process for getting a quote was easy, and the representative was friendly and informative. We were originally looking for quotes for a different remodel project, but decided to complete a cheaper project now rather than wait longer to complete the more expensive remodel. During the initial quote process, we were told they could give special pricing that day for cement work because they were low on work in that area at the time. I did mention the coupon, and had it on the counter visible while discussing with the rep our various projects and our ideas for cement out front. We were given their regular price, and then their "best and final price" if we signed the contract same day. We agreed and moved forward with scheduling the job for the cement work. I should have done the math at the consultation, but realized after payment that the "best and final" price was not even the 10% discount that we had been given on the coupon. We were soon contacted by the project manager Patrick to schedule the job. He called twice more to delay our job due to other jobs taking longer than expected. Once our job was finally scheduled and happening, the crew arrived on time and made quick work of the demo and setting the forms. However, the forms were not set right, and they blamed the inadequate photos and unclear instructions that their own company had provided them. The error was fixed the next morning before pouring, but was still not the width that we had originally agreed on. They cut through a few sprinkles, but fixed the line. During demolition they also crushed our sewage cap and said they would be back out in a few days to replace it with a new one, and would also rebury our cable cords. We noticed after the crew had left for the day, that they had scraped the excess cement from their shoes or tools onto our sprinkler head, which had dried cement plugging the holes, and we had to clean and pick out, which was very frustrating. A few days later, someone came by to rebury the cable, but no new sewer cap. After a week had gone by, I reached back out to Patrick and he was unaware that it hadn't been fixed and said it would be done in the next couple of days. Another week went by with no sewer cap, and no contact from the company. We then started seeing sewage coming out of the open broken hole into our yard. The County came out and assessed the line, and found that several large parts of the plastic sewer cap had gone down into the line and caused a clog. They fixed the issue and replaced our sewer cap. All in all, the driveway looks nice and we are glad we got it redone, but I don't know if I would use this company again. Which is unfortunate, because we were really hoping to find a company we could continue to use for other projects and have a trusted relationship with.< /text>

< review>
I have had three projects done by Reliable Home Improvement.  The first was replacing the countertops in my kitchen.  They did a great job.  I like the fact that they make sure that all state and city codes are met.  They do little extra things like replace all the kitchen electrical outlets and plates so they all match.  They even came with me to Arizona Tile to pick out quartz slab for the counter tops.

The second project was replacing two sliding glass doors.  They were removed and installed in one day.  The doors also came with screens.

The third project was a complete remodel of the hall bathroom.  You get complete freedom to choose flooring, vanity, countertops, paint, mirrors, tubs, and faucets.  The company gives you recommendations of where to shop, but you are free to shop as you please.  If you ask they will give you some recommendations which I have found to be useful.  Occasionally, there will be restrictions due to codes.  I love the way my bathroom looks now.  This was all done during covid, and I felt no pressure when the vanity I wanted took a couple of months to arrive at my house.

I am now in the process of having my Master Bathroom remodeled by  Reliable.

Some of the things that I like about the company are the following.  They do not start a project until all items have arrived.  Once they start the project, they stay until the project is finished.  They clean up after themselves each day.  They do not smoke on the property.  Except in a rare circumstance, they do not use foul language.  They are punctual.
Everyone is very polite.

A warning.  Reliable warns that there will be dust, but if you are having tile work done, I suggest you cover up any furniture, curtains and blinds.  The tile dust is thick and can be difficult to remove.<//review>

<Review>My husband and I had 3 major projects done on our home over the winter. First we had new flooring installed. We chose luxury vinyl plank (golden oak) style. After looking at a slab flooring throughout our home for 6 years after some flooding, we finally had something nice to look at. I'm still admiring these floors. Our whole house was done, including closets. A couple of mishaps though while the work was being done, one being they scuffed a good 2 foot area while sliding the hutch back into place in the dining room. BUT they were able to buff it out with a solution specifically made for that. The other issue was I believe it was Juan, he broke one of the ceramic bathroom tiles while working around that doorway in that area and didn't tell us about it. They had to glue the strip across the doorway and had blue painters tape in place for 24 hours. So the following day when I removed the tape, I saw the 3 cracks. Shawn the owner did offer to have his guys replace that tile but at the time we didn't know where they were stored so we said forget it. Also the furniture in the living room they had put back before I had a chance to sweep the floors or vacuum up the pieces left behind when they swept. I wanted to vacuum it all up but the crew wanted to have the living room done so we'd have a room to enjoy while they worked on the rest of the house. Also the baseboards were left with smudges, scratches, and some small chipped areas that Juan's crew filled in with caulking. Every single room had such dirty baseboards that my husband and I decided to paint over them. They were so ugly, they looked 20 years old with family scuff marks over time. They did not look brand new at all. But hey, we have new flooring and baseboards but I do have my work cut out for me moving the furniture out in every room to properly clean the floors and paint the baseboards.
That said, next job was new windows. Anlin, tinted windows. They work so well to keep the heat out, I'm freezing in the winter time even with the curtains open, no heat comes in from the sun. But now that it's summer time, I do feel "some" heat from the sun but it's nothing to complain about. Jerry did a great job. He had no idea what he was in for when he reviewed the job. We had 9 windows and the slider door replaced. The only mishap there was a long gash on the dining room windowsill which can be filled, sanded, and repainted. Oh and come to find out, evidently when Jeremy gave us the estimate for the windows, they had trim all around them. But when the windows were delivered, none of them  had the trim. I guess with the stucco it wouldn't work with that type of trim. Thanks Jeremy for a big disappointment in that area because I only chose those windows (style) because of the trim. We decided to get a new screen door and a new porch light to match the rest of our new looking home. Overall we are pleased with the work. Our home looks so much nicer outside and inside. The stucco color was matched perfectly AND to make it up to us with the little mishaps here and there, they offered to apply a coat of stucco around the whole house! They offered us a choice of texture and we chose the small style. What a difference! We just love it. They ALSO replaced all the drain spouts without cost to us AND they painted them too to match the house. I have to say that I really enjoyed getting to know the guys and gals at Reliable. They are funny and friendly, like family. I would recommend them to anyone and we will consider them for future projects. We got great deals on every job. Totally satisfied. <Text>Reliable just completed landscaping our totally barren and neglected back yard. This is our second project with Reliable, having done our front landscape two years ago. The experience and results from that project made it a no-brainer to sign them up again. Tim Azevedo, our Design Consultant from the front-yard project kept in touch with us, knowing that we'd eventually want to landscape the rear yard. When Tim presented us their project proposal, we didn't bother to consider other contractors. Patrick Bedford returned as our Project Manager, and our Reliable team was back in place.

Tim drafted his original design and worked diligently with us to refine features until we had our desired design. As the crew started the initial construction, we came up with a few "tweaks", some required the crew to undo/redo some work. Patrick and the entire Reliable team worked with us, never made an issue over our last-minute changes, and completed
everything that we asked for.

The result is a back yard that is nothing short of a dream! The tinted, stamped, and sealed concrete is spectacular; the poured-concrete curved bench in the back corner makes the ideal setting for a fire pit. The two turf areas punctuate the concrete, giving the space an oasis-like appearance. The custom patio cover completes the space and enhances our house's rear elevation.

There isn't a single spot of this job that we would change. Tim, Patrick, and the entire Reliable team made it two-for-two on our landscaping. We're so happy that we just signed up for the third, and last, piece: driveway and front sidewalk/porch to match the rear yard concrete.<//Text><user>103203298795144397760</user>< gmap_id>

There is no way I would ever deal with this company again.  I was going to give them a chance to bid on a patio cover and cement replacement of a sidewalk I needed done, but I think they are way too expensive for me.</Text>

<rate>3</rate><text>They repainted our house and did an excellent job with both the prep and the actual painting. They were very concerned with getting the job done right the first time. A little on the expensive side, but well worth it.

They said they could do the drywall - no problem but would have to check with their "floor guy" on the flooring repair.  They even offered to remove the drywall for free. He did fine but we had to wait to have another person come in to do the joint taping and texturing. I appreciate that there was no charge for the job, but nearly 2 months to do a job that could have been done in less than a few days!  It became very clear that Reliable is a great contractor to use if you have a big job, like $10,000 but if your job is small, they try to fit you in when their people have the time. <userid>113082460938487002671<//userid>< user_name>
Jeff Jensen<//user_name>
<time>1375416768044</time>< rating>
1</rating>
<Review>normally buy basic supplies at Office Depot Thousand Oaks and I decided to try them for computer repair on my older HP desktop. After waiting 15-20 minutes for assistance the only technician in the store looked at my HP and stated it could be the motherboard but a system restore might fix the problem. I was quoted $100 for a system restore and guaranteed if it did not fix my problem I would receive a 50% credit. Seemed a reasonable risk. Picked up my HP a few days later and it worked great for 1-day and then completely shut down. Took the unit back and was told they are not equipped to diagnose hardware problems, been good to know earlier.
Let the unit for further diagnose with and was instructed to call them. Called Thursday and spoke with Nathan the store manager and after mentioning the 50% refund was told that's the first time I've ever heard of that. Nathan promised to check with the original technician and call me back Monday. Tuesday I called, Nathan was gone for the day. explained the whole issue to someone else and was promised another callback. < Review>

Well, they (my Co-Workers) are so right to put Toppers Pizza in high regards and praise.

Forewarned that the Pizza is worth the price and that price point $12 for a small pizza "Toppers Combo Top Hit Combo".  On this "combo", I requested as Half "combo" and Hawaiian style (Canadian Bacon & Pineaple).  The toppings go to edge of the crust and plentiful and tasteful it was.

I also sprang for some Hot Wings.  The selection of sauce rubs include (Asian, Lemon Peper, BBQ and Nashville Hot). Selecting the Nashville Hot had a ting of sweet upon the bit of that crispy flavorful skin and then... that heat from the fried in sauce bites me back.

Now, there is similar pizza of this style in Northern California Silicon Valley called "Stuft Pizza" very similar to that of "Toppers".   In fact, they are very alike and both establishments are on equal playing field. So either in Ventura area or Fremont ( East Bay) areas, stop by the best pizzas of their respective areas.

I have to rate Toppers Pizza at 4 Stars.  Although, very delicious, a little high price point, it was worth it.  However, unlike Stuft Pizza, they didn't honor Armed Forces or Veteran's status.  Otherwise, the 5 Stars would have been a given.   I recommend it.< /Review></record></dataset><record>

< text>
Good to have a local depot which, oddly, is not listed on the DHL "Find a Location" website. A few things to keep in mind:
- Be patient - things move slow. Staff seems inexperienced.
- Generate, print  and pay for your label online ahead of time if you can. It will still take a while, but this will help
- Your packages will be opened and inspected (TSA requirements) so don't bother taping up your boxes in advance
- There are no shipping supplies like you might find at a FedEx or UPS Store
- Counter is open until 8pm but drop-off by 5pm if you want it to go out same day<//text>

< Text>
I haven't been here in a few years.  I was very disappointed on my shrimp and fish tacos.  They shrunk them to a third of its original size.  These type of tacos don't go on the tiny corn tortillas, but the normal bigger size.  There were only two tiny shrimps on my shrimp taco and  a 2"-2.5" piece of fish on my fish taco.  The flavor remain delicious.  They also had the option of having them as a combo with rice and beans.  Not all Mexican food goes with rice and beans.  These tacos go well by themselves, perhaps accompanied with cucumber in lemon juice.  They're supposed to be a "fresh-beachy" type of meal, the beans and rice warm it up.  I don't think I'll be buying the tacos from here again.< /Text>
